<html>
	<head>
		<title>Date & Time Page</title>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-us">
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
	</head>
	<body>
		<p><IMG alt="" src="DateTime.jpg"></p>
		<p>This is the Date &amp; Time page of the Brainchild configuration program. With it 
			you can change the way time and date strings are formatted by the <b>EditInsertDate</b>
			and <b>EditInsertTime</b> commands. The various settings are explaned below:</p>
		<table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellPadding="1">
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Date format</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can enter the string used to format the date output of the <b>EditInsertDate</b>
					command. Format elements allowed are:<br>
					<table border="1" cellpadding="2" width="100%" cellspacing="1">
						<tr>
							<td width="10%" bgcolor="#e4e4e4"><b>Element</b></td>
							<td width="90%" bgcolor="#e4e4e4"><b>Meaning</b></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">d</td>
							<td width="90%">Day of the month as a number without a leading 0 digit for single digit 
								days.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">dd</td>
							<td width="90%">Day of the month as a number with a leading 0 digit for single digit 
								days.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">ddd</td>
							<td width="90%">Day of the week as a three-letter abbrevation.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">dddd</td>
							<td width="90%">Day of the week as it's full name.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">M</td>
							<td width="90%">Month as a number without a leading 0 digit for single digit months.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">MM</td>
							<td width="90%">Month as a number with a leading 0 digit for single digit months.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">MMM</td>
							<td width="90%">Month as a three-letter abbrevation.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">MMMM</td>
							<td width="90%">Month as it's full name.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">y</td>
							<td width="90%">Year as last two digits without a leading zero for years less than 10.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">yy</td>
							<td width="90%">Year as last two digits with a leading zero for years less than 10.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">yyyy</td>
							<td width="90%">Year represented by four digits.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">gg</td>
							<td width="90%">Period/era string.</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
					<p>Characters enclosed in single quotes will be inserted into the formatted output 
						exactly as they occur in the format string.</p>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Time format</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can enter the string used to format the time output of the <b>EditInsertTime</b>
					command. Format elements allowed are:<br>
					<table border="1" cellpadding="2" width="100%" cellspacing="1">
						<tr>
							<td width="10%" bgcolor="#e4e4e4"><b>Element</b></td>
							<td width="90%" bgcolor="#e4e4e4"><b>Meaning</b></td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">h</td>
							<td width="90%">Hours without a leading zero for single digit hours. (12-hour clock)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">hh</td>
							<td width="90%">Hours with a leading zero for single digit hours. (12-hour clock)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">H</td>
							<td width="90%">Hours without a leading zero for single digit hours. (24-hour clock)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">HH</td>
							<td width="90%">Hours with a leading zero for single digit hours. (24-hour clock)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">m</td>
							<td width="90%">Minutes without a leading zero for single digit minutes.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">mm</td>
							<td width="90%">Minute with a leading zero for single digit minutes.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">s</td>
							<td width="90%">Seconds without a leading zero for single digit seconds.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">ss</td>
							<td width="90%">Seconds with a leading zero for single digit secods.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">t</td>
							<td width="90%">Single character time marker string, such as A or P.</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td width="10%">tt</td>
							<td width="90%">Multicharacter time marker string, such as AM or PM</td>
						</tr>
					</table>
					<p>Characters enclosed in single quotes will be inserted into the formatted output 
						exactly as they occur in the format string.</p>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Sample date</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can see an example of the formatted output as it would be when 
					inserted into the text by the <b>EditInsertDate</b> command.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Sample time</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can see an example of the formatted output as it would be when 
					inserted info the text by the <b>EditInsertTime</b> command.</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</body>
</html>
